1.title: Blind Auditions, Part 1
1.plot: "Blind auditions" are held in front of a celebrity panel of music coaches including, Christina Aguilera, Cee Lo Green, Adam Levine and Blake Shelton who each compete to select eight vocalists for their individual teams.

2.title: Blind Auditions, Part 2
2.plot: Part 2 of the Blind Auditions, More Artists take a shot at impressing the coaches with only their voice. This episode also includes a "Second Chance Round" where previous failed contestants and new contestants take one more shot at impressing the coaches.

6.title: The Battles, Part 4
6.plot: The "battle rounds" continue and the coaches join forces with music industry professionals for guidance. Christina Aguilera teams up with singer/songwriter Sia Furler, Adam Levine with music producer Adam Blackstone, Cee Lo Green with singer Monica, and Blake Shelton with Grammy-winning singer Reba. In this phase the coaches will pit two of their own team members against each other in a dueling duet. After the vocal face-off, each coach, with the help of their adviser, must choose which of his/her singers are the strongest and four vocalists will advance to the live ...

7.title: Live Show, Quarter-Finals #1
7.plot: In this live performance phase of the competition, the top vocalists from each team will compete against each other during a live broadcast. America will vote to save one vocalist on each team, leaving coaches Christina Aguilera, Cee Lo Green, Adam Levine and Blake Shelton to decide during the live show who they will save and who will not move on. Finally, each coach will have their best vocalist left standing to compete in the finale for the chance to win the grand prize of a $100,000 and a recording contract.

The strongest vocalists from across the country compete to be selected by one of the coaches and fight for a chance to win the title of being named "The Voice."

1.title: The Blind Auditions Premiere
1.plot: In the season 10 premiere, coaches Blake Shelton, Pharrell Williams, Adam Levine and Christina Aguilera battle for America's best undiscovered singer in the blind auditions.

2.title: The Blind Auditions Premiere, Part 2
2.plot: The Blind Auditions continue as Pharrell Williams, Adam Levine, Christina Aguilera and Blake Shelton search for the best singers to recruit for their teams.

3.title: The Blind Auditions, Part 3
3.plot: Pharrell Williams, Adam Levine, Christina Aguilera and Blake Shelton continue to battle for the strongest singers in another round of blind auditions.

4.title: The Blind Auditions, Part 4
4.plot: Pharrell Williams, Adam Levine, Christina Aguilera and Blake Shelton go toe-to-toe in the blind auditions to secure the best singers for their teams.

5.title: The Best of the Blind Auditions
5.plot: Carson Daly recaps the best of Season 10's blind auditions, giving us an overview of the talented singers Adam Levine, Christina Aguilera, Pharrell Williams and Blake Shelton added to their teams.

6.title: Blinds End and Battles Begin
6.plot: Coaches Blake Shelton, Pharrell Williams, Adam Levine and Christina Aguilera complete their teams and kick off the battle rounds.

7.title: The Battles Premiere, Part 2
7.plot: On the second night of battle duets, the coaches continue the process of refining their teams - and only the best of the best will make it.

8.title: The Battles, Part 3
8.plot: Coaches Adam Levine, Christina Aguilera, Blake Shelton and Pharrell Williams watch more of their vocalists battle to stay in the competition. Featuring advisors Patti LaBelle, Gwen Stefani, Sean 'Diddy' Combs (Sean "Diddy" Combs, aka Puff Daddy), and Tori Kelly.

9.title: The Battles, Part 4
9.plot: It's go big or go home as the remaining artists put it all on the stage in the final night of battles for Coaches Adam Levine, Pharrell Williams, Christina Aguilera and Blake Shelton.

10.title: The Knockouts Premiere
10.plot: The coaches enlist influential pop star Miley Cyrus to help prepare the artists for the thrilling knockout round.

11.title: The Knockouts Premiere, Part 2
11.plot: The incredible performances and shocking cuts continue as the remaining artists sing to survive to the live shows. Superstar Miley Cyrus serves as key advisor.

12.title: The Knockouts, Part 3
12.plot: The coaches once again get help from key advisor Miley Cyrus before making the final cuts to solidify their teams for the live shows - and only one steal remains.

13.title: The Road to the Live Shows
13.plot: Relive this season's best performances so far as we take a look back at how the coaches built their teams for the live shows. Plus, see never-before-seen moments between the coaches and advisors.

imdb.plot outline: There are four coaches, who are all famous in the music industry. During the blind auditions these coaches will turn around in their chairs when they hear a performer they want in their team. If there are more coaches who want a performer, he or she gets to choose who they want as their coach. During the battles there will be two contestants from the same team up against eachother. The coach then has to choose one of them to get through to the live shows.
imdb.title: The Voice
plot: Four famous musicians search for the best voices in America and will mentor these singers to become artists. America will decide which singer will be worthy of the grand prize.::Anonymous

There are four coaches, who are all famous in the music industry. During the blind auditions these coaches will turn around in their chairs when they hear a performer they want in their team. If there are more coaches who want a performer, he or she gets to choose who they want as their coach. During the battles there will be two contestants from the same team up against eachother. The coach then has to choose one of them to get through to the live shows.::immevangorp
synopsis:
"The Voice" - Semi-Finals Results Show - May 1, 2012We get some recap from Carson of last night's show and some blah-blah-blah from the judges about how it is both amazing and sad to see one member of their team advance and one go home.
